biography: Inspired by Janis Joplin , Rival Sons and Hozier, Children of the Sün embody both the carefree and reflective sides of classic rock music with folk-vibes. Following their 2018 success in the Swedish music competition Livekarusellen, the band released a self-titled EP and later came under the wing of The Sign Records, joining acts such as Hällas ,MaidaVale , Skraeckoedlan, and The Hawkins . In 2019 the band released their first full-length album which was received with great love from the audience and the vinyl sold out just a few months after the release. They´re now back with their sophomore album "Roots". A album that shows depth and growth to the bands sound. Read more on Last.fm.
